4. Field Observations

Institute researchers embedded themselves inside corporate communication environments and observed the following recurring behaviors:

4.1 The Spontaneous Apology Reflex (SAR)

Occurs when a sentence contains more than one confident adjective.

Example:

“This is a dangerously flawed model.”

Automatically becomes:

“This model may have some limitations worth exploring.”

4.2 The Confidence Dilution Effect (CDE)

Statements follow a predictable dilution pattern:

Draft	Final Version
“This will fail.”	“This may face challenges.”
“This is wrong.”	“This may not be accurate.”
“This is misleading.”	“This could be interpreted in different ways.”
“This is a serious problem.”	“This is a non-trivial consideration.”

4.3 The Passive Voice Migration (PVM)

Responsibility disappears linguistically:
	•	“We made a mistake.”
becomes
	•	“Mistakes were made.”

This is known as Agency Evaporation Through Grammar (AETG).

